text.tspan: Political regime type vs. Human Rights Score, 2017
Shown is each country's political regime type plotted against its Human Rights Score. The four possible political
regime types are 0 = "Closed autocracy", 1 = "Electoral autocracy", 2 = "Electoral democracy", 3 = "Liberal
democracy"; while the Human Rights Scores range from around âˆ’3.8 to around 5.4 (the higher the better).
Source: V-Dem (2018), Schnakenberg and Fariss (2014), Fariss (2019)
